Aim

To create and manipulate arrays using NumPy functions.

Theory

NumPy is used for numerical operations and array processing.
It provides fast and memory-efficient array handling.

Program
import numpy as np

# Create array
arr = np.arange(1, 13)

# Reshape array
reshaped = arr.reshape(3, 4)

# Display arrays
print("Original Array:")
print(arr)

print("\nReshaped Array:")
print(reshaped)

# Shape and sum
print("\nShape:", reshaped.shape)
print("Sum:", np.sum(reshaped))
print("Maximum:", np.max(reshaped))
print("Minimum:", np.min(reshaped))


Procedure
Open Jupyter Notebook.
Import NumPy library.
Create array using arange().
Store values in variable.
Use reshape() to change dimensions.
Display original array.
Display reshaped array.
Find shape using shape.
Find sum, max, and min values.
Execute and verify output.


